HEADWORD: Tentiginous
<hw>Ten*tig"i*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tentigo</ets>, <ets>-inis</ets>, a tension, lecherousness, fr.
<ets>tendere</ets>, <ets>tentum</ets>, to stretch.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Stiff; stretched; strained.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lustful, or pertaining to lust.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tentmaker</ent>⟦br⟧
